cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of local binary patterns (LBPs) in image and video analysis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. LBPs are also used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The paper also mentions the development of new variants of LBPs to improve their performance, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses future challenges for research, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
